# --- Local dev (npm run dev) ---
# "Generate Widget" (the sparkle bubble) needs an OpenAI key. Copy this file
# to .env for local dev. In dev, generation runs in-process via the Vite
# middleware twin (an in-memory job map), so no Supabase is needed locally.
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# Optional — the generator defaults to gpt-5 with live web search.
# OPENAI_MODEL=gpt-5
# Optional — reasoning effort for generation (default "medium"). Generation is
# async now, so there's no synchronous-timeout reason to keep it low.
# OPENAI_REASONING_EFFORT=medium
# Optional — the runtime widget.ai() data lookup defaults to gpt-5-mini / low
# effort (kept snappy). Override independently of the generator:
# OPENAI_DATA_MODEL=gpt-5-mini
# OPENAI_DATA_REASONING_EFFORT=low

# --- Production build (Netlify) ---
# Generation runs as an async job on Supabase edge functions; the frontend
# calls them directly, so the build needs the project URL + publishable key.
# (These are public by design.) Set OPENAI_API_KEY as a *Supabase function
# secret*, not here — see the README "Deploying" section.
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxxxxxxx.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_...
